Package: CompRisksBenchmaRk
Type: Package
Title: Benchmarking Framework for Competing Risks Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("VallejosGroup", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "placeholder@example.com")
Description: A unified framework for fitting, predicting, and benchmarking
    competing risks survival models. Provides a model registry for registering
    custom models, a nested cross-validation engine for unbiased hyperparameter
    tuning and evaluation, and a comprehensive set of performance metrics
    including time-varying Brier scores, integrated Brier scores, AUC,
    C-index, and calibration measures. Built-in model wrappers cover the
    Fine-Gray regression (FGR), penalised Fine-Gray (FGRP), cause-specific
    Cox proportional hazards (csCPH), random survival forests (RSF), and the
    Vertical Model. Supports missing data via median/mode or MICE imputation,
    and provides plotting utilities for calibration curves and decision curve
    analysis.
